# 📚 What I Learned

This project taught me how JavaScript and CSS can work together to create interactive UI effects.

Instead of directly changing styles, JavaScript updates CSS variables, allowing CSS to handle rendering efficiently.

I also learned how to create reusable SCSS code using Mixins, animate elements with custom easing, generate random characters using JavaScript, and restore the original text after an animation.

This project improved my understanding of DOM manipulation, CSS animations, string manipulation, and interactive frontend design.

---

# 🔮 Future Improvements

* Reveal original letters one by one instead of all at once.
* Add GSAP animations.
* Support touch devices.
* Add sound effects on hover.
* Improve accessibility.
* Optimize animations using requestAnimationFrame().

