# 📌 Brutally Honest Review

### ✅ What I did well

* Successfully combined SCSS and JavaScript.
* Used CSS Variables instead of hardcoded values.
* Built an interactive UI instead of a static page.
* Applied reusable SCSS Mixins.
* Practiced string manipulation with `split()`, `map()`, and `join()`.

### ❌ Mistakes I made

* Created variables (`tops`, `h2`) that were never used.
* Repeated hover styles for all three panels instead of making them reusable.
* Used `setInterval()` for the text animation, which could be optimized further.
* Some code can be refactored into reusable functions.

### 🤔 Why these mistakes happened

I focused on making the project work first and cleaned up the code later. This is common while learning, but the next step is writing cleaner, more reusable code.

### 📈 Did I apply previous concepts?

Yes.

This project combines concepts from previous DOM practice:

* DOM Selection
* Event Listeners
* CSS Positioning
* Flexbox
* Hover Effects
* JavaScript Timers
* String Methods

Instead of copying only syntax, I combined multiple concepts into one interactive project.

### 🎯 What should I improve before the next project?

* Write reusable JavaScript functions.
* Avoid unused variables.
* Reduce duplicate CSS.
* Learn `requestAnimationFrame()` for smoother animations.
* Practice more advanced text reveal logic.
* Keep improving code readability and naming conventions.
