Why in this project?
::after overlay ko poori screen cover karani thi. inset: 0 se wo parent ke charo taraf automatically fit ho gaya.

9. cubic-bezier()

Creates a custom animation timing.

Why in this project?
Normal ease ki jagah custom animation speed use ki gayi, jisse panel expand aur heading animation aur smooth aur premium feel deti hai.
# 🧩 JavaScript Logic Explained

### **1. `style.setProperty()`**

Used to update CSS Variables (`--x` and `--y`) from JavaScript.

**Why in this project?**
Mouse ki current position (`clientX` & `clientY`) ko CSS Variables me store kiya gaya. CSS ne un variables ko `radial-gradient()` me use kiya, isliye spotlight mouse ke saath move karta hai.

---

### **2. `split()`**

Converts a string into an array.

**Why in this project?**
Heading (`"EXPLORE"`) ko letter-by-letter todna tha. `split('')` ne string ko array bana diya, taaki har character ko alag se change kiya ja sake.

---

### **3. `map()`**

Runs on every item of an array and returns a new array.

**Why in this project?**
`split()` se bane har letter ki jagah `map()` ne ek random character return kiya. Isse poori heading random letters me convert ho gayi.

---

### **4. `join()`**

Converts an array back into a string.

**Why in this project?**
`map()` ke baad result ek array tha. `join('')` ne us array ko dobara ek complete word bana diya, jise screen par dikhaya gaya.

---

### **5. `setInterval()`**

Runs the same code repeatedly after a fixed time.

**Why in this project?**
Har **90ms** baad naye random letters generate hue. Isi wajah se heading continuously change hoti hui animation jaisi dikhti hai.

---

### **6. `clearInterval()`**

Stops a running `setInterval()`.

**Why in this project?**
2 seconds ke baad random letters ko stop karna tha. `clearInterval()` ne animation ko band kar diya.

---

### **7. `setTimeout()`**

Runs code only once after a specified time.

**Why in this project?**
2 seconds baad random animation stop karke original text wapas dikhana tha. Isliye `setTimeout()` use kiya gaya.

---

### **8. `forEach()`**

Loops through every element of a NodeList or array.

**Why in this project?**
Page me **3 `<h1>`** the. `querySelectorAll()` ne unhe NodeList me store kiya aur `forEach()` ne har heading par same hover animation apply kar diya.

---

# 📌 Final Logic

```text
Hover on H1
      │
      ▼
Original Text Save
      │
      ▼
split() → Array
      │
      ▼
map() → Random Letters
      │
      ▼
join() → String
      │
      ▼
setInterval() → Repeat every 90ms
      │
      ▼
2 Seconds Complete
      │
      ▼
clearInterval()
      │
      ▼
setTimeout()
      │
      ▼
Original Text Restore
```
